benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search - Search custom fields by type, name and optional value

covered: Valid Request: TC01 demonstrates retrieval with no parameters; TC02-TC07 cover valid parameter combinations (objectType, fieldName, fieldValue).
Empty Response: TC11 and TC28 verify handling when no data matches or when the database is empty.
Pagination: TC07 exercises offset/limit; TC21/TC22 test boundary conditions with large datasets; TC30/TC31 touch performance under load.
Query Parameters: Comprehensive coverage of valid/invalid combinations, extra parameters ignored (TC12), invalid values (TC13-TC16), and partial input (TC37).
Audit Integration: FULL/MINIMAL/NONE variations (TC08-TC10) and integration with audit log service (TC32-TC33).
Security & Input Validation: SQL injection test (TC19) and XSS test (TC20).
Regression & Backward Compatibility: FieldName filtering regression (TC25), FULL audit response fix (TC26), and objectType-only compatibility (TC27).
State Variation: Empty database (TC28) and partially populated database (TC29).
Performance Coverage: Basic and peak load tests (TC24, TC30, TC31).
Documentation & Error Messaging: API documentation accessibility (TC34) and descriptive errors (TC35).
Resilience: Recovery from transient network failure (TC36).
Partial Input Coverage: Scenarios with only some parameters provided (TC37).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling tests are not present.
Caching headers and caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) are not tested.
403 Forbidden scenarios (insufficient privileges) are not explicitly tested (only 401 covered).
Some deeper data integrity checks across dependent services beyond audit log integration are not covered.
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests to verify behavior under burst traffic and validate throttling responses.
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching semantics.
Add tests for 403 Forbidden to cover scenarios with insufficient privileges.
Enhance cross-service data consistency tests to cover more audit-related edge cases and degraded service scenarios.
